{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Psa|7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","chapter":7,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":1,"text":"Lord my God, I seek refuge in you; save me from all my pursuers and rescue me,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":2,"text":"or they will tear me like a lion, ripping me apart with no one to rescue me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":3,"text":"Lord my God, if I have done this, if there is injustice on my hands,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":4,"text":"if I have done harm to one at peace with me or have plundered my adversary without cause,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":5,"text":"may an enemy pursue and overtake me; may he trample me to the ground and leave my honor in the dust. Selah","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":6,"text":"Rise up, Lord, in your anger; lift yourself up against the fury of my adversaries; awake for me; you have ordained a judgment.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":7,"text":"Let the assembly of peoples gather around you; take your seat on high over it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":8,"text":"The Lord judges the peoples; vindicate me, Lord, according to my righteousness and my integrity.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":9,"text":"Let the evil of the wicked come to an end, but establish the righteous. The one who examines the thoughts and emotions is a righteous God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":10,"text":"My shield is with God, who saves the upright in heart.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":11,"text":"God is a righteous judge and a God who shows his wrath every day.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":12,"text":"If anyone does not repent, he will sharpen his sword; he has strung his bow and made it ready.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":13,"text":"He has prepared his deadly weapons; he tips his arrows with fire.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":14,"text":"See, the wicked one is pregnant with evil, conceives trouble, and gives birth to deceit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:7:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":7,"verse":15,"text":"He dug a pit and hollowed it ou